  <language>en_US</language>
  <keyword>svd</keyword>
  <short_description>Singular Value Decomposition.</short_description>
  <syntax>
    <syntax_item>s = svd(M)</syntax_item>
    <syntax_item>[U, S, V] = svd(M)</syntax_item>
    <syntax_item>[U, S, V] = svd(M, 0)</syntax_item>
    <syntax_item>[U, S, V] = svd(M, 'econ')</syntax_item>
  </syntax>
  <param_input>
    <param_input_item>
      <param_name>M</param_name>
      <param_description
      >a numeric value: matrix (double or single)</param_description>
    </param_input_item>
  </param_input>
  <param_output>
    <param_output_item>
      <param_name>s</param_name>
      <param_description
      >real vector (singular values) by descending order.</param_description>
    </param_output_item>
    <param_output_item>
      <param_name>U</param_name>
      <param_description>left singular values.</param_description>
    </param_output_item>
    <param_output_item>
      <param_name>S</param_name>
      <param_description
      >real diagonal matrix (singular values)</param_description>
    </param_output_item>
    <param_output_item>
      <param_name>V</param_name>
      <param_description>right singular values.</param_description>
    </param_output_item>
  </param_output>
  <description>
    <p><b>svd</b> computes the Singular Value Decomposition of a matrix.</p>
    <p>For an</p>
    <latex>m \times n</latex>
    <p>matrix <b>M</b>, the SVD is:</p>
    <latex>M = U\Sigma V^T</latex>
    <p>where:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><latex>U</latex>is an</li>
      <latex>m \times m</latex>
      <p>unitary matrix (left singular vectors)</p>
      <li><latex>\Sigma</latex>is an</li>
      <latex>m \times n</latex>
      <p>diagonal matrix with non-negative real numbers (singular values)</p>
      <li><latex>V^T</latex>is an</li>
      <latex>n \times n</latex>
      <p>unitary matrix (right singular vectors)</p>
    </ul>
    <p>The singular values</p>
    <latex>\sigma_i</latex>
    <p>are arranged in decreasing order:</p>
    <latex>\sigma_1 \geq \sigma_2 \geq \ldots \geq 0</latex>
  </description>
